commitResults.messageTitle: Implemented basic Greet, Echo of user input and Exit on "bye" input
commitResults.messageBody: Added UserInterface class to handle user input and pretty printing

commitResults.messageTitle: Implemented Add and List tasks
Implemented Mark as Done
Added a convenience method to UserInterface class, createStringJoiner.
commitResults.messageBody: Returned StringJoiner instance uses the platform's newline separator and can be initialized with a string.

commitResults.messageTitle: Implemented ToDos, Events, Deadlines
Implemented Handle Errors via exceptions
Added support for deleting tasks from the list
Updated Task subclass constructors to support serialization/unserialization
Added support for serialization/unserialization via TaskSerializer class.
commitResults.messageBody: DukeException now supports Chained Exception via a new constructor. Used by TaskSerializer.java's FileIOException/wrapping of Java IOException.

commitResults.messageTitle: Duke now loads Tasks from "./data/duke.txt" and terminates on error if necessary
Duke now saves Tasks to "./data/duke.txt" whenever the task list changes
Duke now understands dates and times, parsing for Deadlines and Events in the "d/M/yyyy HHmm" format and displaying them when needed in the same format.
Fixed inheritance hierarchy for DoneTokenParseError and TypeTokenParseError exception classes
Preliminary work to enable Duke instances
Moved Duke.formatTask static method to UserInterface class
TaskSerializer instances can now be created to load and save Tasks to a specific file path
Added TaskList class
Rearchitectured Duke
commitResults.messageBody:
Created Command interface and reimplemented Duke's commands as separate classes.
Created Parser class to parse user text input and route to the correct Command implementing class.
Moved and created user interface display elements in UserInterface for common tasks.

commitResults.messageTitle: Renamed UserInterface class to Ui in accordance with CS2103T module requirements
Renamed TaskSerializer class to Storage in accordance with CS2103T module requirements
Modified Gradle settings
Added checkstyle to Gradle configuration
Broke out Command implementing classes to their own separate file
Broke out DukeException subclasses classes to their own separate file
Broke out task serializer exceptions to their own separate files
Modified Gradle settings
Override equals() and hashCode() function on Deadline, Event and Task classes
Added test cases for Storage class
AddCommand instances now trigger arguments parsing on instance creation
commitResults.messageBody: Previously triggered on calling the execute() function

commitResults.messageTitle: Added test cases for Parser class
Added JUnit parameterized tests dependency
Added test cases for Ui class
Added new test case for Parser class, testing for unknown command input
Added a suite of tests for Command subclasses

commitResults.messageTitle: Fixed Ui.createStringJoiner bug where passing in null would initialize it with the string "null"
AddDeadlineTaskCommand parsing is now more robust
commitResults.messageBody:
Enabled two test cases on AddDeadlineTaskCommandTest
– Test case for an exception when the "/by" argument is missing
– Test case for an exception when "/by" is provided but the date time argument is missing

commitResults.messageTitle: AddEventTaskCommand parsing is now more robust
commitResults.messageBody:
Enabled two test cases on AddEventTaskCommandTest
– Test case for an exception when the "/at" argument is missing
– Test case for an exception when "/at" is provided but the date time argument is missing

commitResults.messageTitle: Parser is now more robust and transparently rethrows a DukeException from Command implementing class constructors
Fixed test cases for DeleteCommand and DoneCommand when passed in non numeric input
Duke can now be packaged as a JAR file
Implemented a way to find a task by searching for a keyword
Added test cases for FindTaskCommand
Preliminary coding standard compliance changes
Renamed FileIOException class to FileIoException class for coding style compliance
Conformed AddCommand.instantiateTask's access modifier keyword position to JLS suggestions
Conformed any lines of code longer than 120 characters
Parser.parse now uses if/else for simple commands instead of switch-case due to code style requiring a "default" clause
Marked the variables containing expected results in a few test cases as final
Added JavaDocs to a few methods.
